    <text>
        <body>
              <div type="poem">
                <head type="title"><handShift new="#HANDJR1826-27" script="print" medium="pencil"/>VESUVIUS<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="vesuvius_msv_glosses_contextual.php#VESUVIUSGLOSS"/>
                </head>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>Night had oerspread the restless deep</l>
                    <l>And mortals lay ah long to sleep</l>
                    <l>In proud Pompeii's walls<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="vesuvius_msv_glosses_contextual.php#POMPEIIGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>And Herculaneum<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="vesuvius_msv_glosses_contextual.php#HERCULANEUMGLOSS"/> rested there</l>
                    <l>With all its palaces so fair</l>
                    <l>And all its ancient halls<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="vesuvius_msv_glosses_contextual.php#HERCULANEUMHALLSGLOSS"/></l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>In grandeur rose each column high</l>
                    <l>Each pile majestic braved the sky</l>
                    <l>And there the placid moon</l>
                    <l>Had touched each column tower &#x0026; tree</l>
                    <l>With bright and solemn majesty</l>
                    <l>To be destoryed too soon</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>Lo to the west the rolling sea</l>
                    <l>Moans forth its booming minstrelsy</l>
                    <l>Upon the Italian shore</l>
                    <l>And sings a solemn dirge for those</l>
                    <l>Who when the evening breeze arose</l>
                    <l>Lay down to rise no more</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>There on the plain Vesuvius heaps</l>
                    <l>His giant crags his towering steeps</l>
                    <l>Full dismal dark and drear</l>
                    <l>And as the crater proudly towrs</l>
                    <l>Up to the stars at midnight hours</l>
                    <l>Inspires the soul with fear</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>Hark hark I heard a thundering sound</l>
                    <l>Seeming as if twere under ground</l>
                    <l>Ha how the earth it shakes</l>
                    <l>The moon is lost in murky clouds</l>
                    <l>The stars are wrapped in thickest shrouds</l>
                    <l>And how the mountain quakes</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>Behold a massy vapour creeps</l>
                    <l>Up dark Vesuvius giant steeps</l>
                    <l>It rises towering still</l>
                    <l>And widely spreading darkens night</l>
                    <l>View how it towrs three times the height</l>
                    <l>Of black Vesuvius hill</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>Now through its body dark &#x0026; deep</l>
                    <l>High rising from Vesuvius steep</l>
                    <l>Volcanic lightnings play</l>
                    <l>And then tow'rds Herculaneum fair</l>
                    <l>Adown the rocky sides so bare</l>
                    <l>The lava burnt its way</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>Now oer the landscape darkness spread</l>
                    <l>And hid Vesuvius giant head</l>
                    <l>In black oershadowing night</l>
                    <l>Then came the sounds of woe most deep</l>
                    <l>Borne on the tempest whirlwind sweep</l>
                    <l>And grief and screams and fright</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>Again again red bursts of flame</l>
                    <l>And lava from Vesuvius came</l>
                    <l>Again the mountain shook</l>
                    <l>And bursting forth with thundering sound</l>
                    <l>And shaking all the earth around</l>
                    <l>Forth forth the ashes broke</l>
                </lg>
                <lg tyoe="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>Then sounds of wailing sounds of grief</l>
                    <l>And screams of agony full brief</l>
                    <l>From Herculaneum rose</l>
                    <l>The liquid lava as it rolled</l>
                    <l>Circling them in its burning fold</l>
                    <l>Made short their dying throes</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
